Interface DynamicSet

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BSTDynamicSet, DLLDynamicSet, SkipListDynamicSet

    public interface DynamicSet
    ADT that stores and retrieves Objects according to keys of type KeyType
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Dan Suthers

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void delete(KeyType k)
      Given a key k, removes elements indexed by k from the set.
      void insert(KeyType k, java.lang.Object e)
      Inserts k.getValue() in the set under key k.
      java.lang.Object maximum()
      Finds an Object that has the largest key, and returns a pointer to it, or null if the set is empty.
      java.lang.Object minimum()
      Finds an Object that has the smallest key, and returns a pointer to it, or null if the set is empty.
      java.lang.Object predecessor(KeyType k)
      Finds an Object that has the next smaller key in the set below k, and returns a pointer to it, or null if k is the minimum element.
      java.lang.Object search(KeyType k)
      Finds an Object with key k and returns a pointer to it, or null if not found.
      int size() 
      java.lang.Object successor(KeyType k)
      Finds an Object that has the next larger key in the set above k, and returns a pointer to it, or null if k is the maximum element.
